      "bullets": [
        "Unstable zero-day kernel exploits often crash target systems, inadvertently alerting defenders before attackers can establish persistent backdoors.",
        "Egress network filtering and strict firewall rules block reverse shells from reaching external command-and-control servers during post-compromise phases.",
        "Aggressive endpoint log analysis and file integrity monitoring remain primary defenses to detect anomalous lateral movement attempts early."
      ]
